It's a chain so everyone should be the same for some degree, but this place is special. Friendly service, fast, daily specials (get one for Thursday - it's tasty and easily can be shared). Pretty cheap by DC standards (10-12 for lunch). I haven't seen a lot of tourists mostly office or federals from the nearest buildings. Parking cost the same as the lunch so if you're close - walk.

The bibimbap was spicy because it was made with 3 rounds of red pepper paste. The cucumber soup inside is delicious. Great option near the mall. It is a bit crowded near 12pm but around 1pm gets better. The food is great and the prices are reasonable. For reference, it was cheaper than McDonalds for my family of 5. Highly recommended.

Great lunch spot!! Lots of options to customize your meal (with gluten-free options!) but also have signature bowls if you don't want to build-your-own. They pack your bowl full of ingredients with a good mix of protein and vegetables. You can tell that everything tastes really fresh!  Nice, friendly staff with great service. Wait was quick even with a line. Enjoyed the ambiance, and the bright, simple interior. Will definitely be back!!
Family-owned Korean Bibimbap in a customizable Chipotle order & service format. All the workers were so nice! A unique, quick & very tasty lunch or dinner option! Great value too.

Amazing food with many options to create a dish to your liking!  Food is high quality and delicious - healthy options, as well!  Great location and atmosphere. The staff are extremely kind and provide excellent, timely service. Would highly recommend!

Good enough. I eat here all the time because it is across the street from where i work. If i didn’t work nearby i would say there is zero reason to eat here. I think it caters to those working in he area anyway it’s not a destination restaurant one would travel to. The food is just ok and gets the job done when in a hurry and wanting something that isn’t fast food. If you want a quick bite this is decent. Just do t expect to be wow’d by it.

Fresh and tasty! Korean and raw fish in Chipotle serving format. I got Hawaii Poke (raw tuna in pepper sauce, not spicy) and plain tofu (spicy and teriyaki options) with brown rice. A new favorite spot!
This place has great food, it can be a little pricey depending on your options. Get there by 11:30 before the line gets too long
